### 16 - Related Subnets

IBM Product Manager requires related subnets for supplementary virtual machines, to host applications such as DB2.  These subnets should be within the same resource group and VNet range previously defined.  The network numbers should be IPv4 RFC1918 compliant and prefixed.

Using a virtual network (VNet) prefix /21, with the OpenShift master & worker subnet prefixed /23, then that will leave an additional four (4) /24 prefixes, or eight (8) /25 prefixes available.

This document will use /25 prefixes for the related subnets, e.g.

* 10.11.4.0/25 - Application Gateway Subnet
