#### 19.6 - Create VPN Gateway Root Certificate Data


In a previous step, the root certificate was created in the Privacy Enhanced Mail (PEM) format.

PEM is the most common format for X.509 certificates. A PEM file is a text file containing one or more items in base64 ASCII encoding identified by plain-text headers and footers (i.e. -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE----- and -----END CERTIFICATE-----).

The VPN Gateway requires the public Root Certificate Data to be uploaded as the base64 ASCII encoding of the Distinguished Encoding Rules (DER) format.

DER is a binary encoding for X.509 certificates and private keys. Unlike PEM, DER-encoded files do not contain plain text statements such as -----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----.  DER is a binary format for data structures described by ASN.1.

**_References:_**

* [https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/network/vnet-gateway/root-cert?view=azure-cli-latest#az_network_vnet_gateway_root_cert_create](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/cli/azure/network/vnet-gateway/root-cert?view=azure-cli-latest#az_network_vnet_gateway_root_cert_create)
* [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Privacy-Enhanced_Mail](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Privacy-Enhanced_Mail)
* [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X.690#DER_encoding](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/X.690#DER_encoding)
* [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASN.1](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ASN.1)


**_Command(s):_**

```bash
az network vnet-gateway root-cert create --gateway-name ${ARO_VGW_NAME} --resource-group ${ARO_RESOURCE_GROUP_NAME} --name "${ARO_VGW_PKI_ROOT_CRT_FILE_NAME}" --public-cert-data "$(openssl x509 -in "${ARO_VGW_PKI_ROOT_CRT_FILE}" -outform der | base64 -w0)"
```

